## **Final Cut Pro**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The reason why videophile or Video Professionals buy a Mac is to get their hands dirty on its one of industry standard of Video Editing tools available.

The name itself lures out the artists who are willing to spend that hefty price tag of $399 for making their videos on the Internet worth watching.

All the top Video industry officials uses this software for making a videos which stand out from others.

It is purely designed around Mac Hardware &amp; also supports the Retina Resolution of the Macbook Pro. You can edit 1080p video pixel by pixel 1:1 ratio on the Macbook Pro &amp; this have space left for other tools on the left hand side panel.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

It also uses Dedicated Graphic cards for extra juice out of the video processing &amp; it has support for faster SSD speeds. So all the seeks, thumnail generation &amp; grubs are lighting fast.

In Mac OS X El Capitan they also have support for Direct API Metal for Mac Applications. Which supposedly gives better draw calls from dedicated GPU thus leading to faster video processing.

Less overhead for CPU with GPU communications using Metal API developed by Apple for latest OS-X.

As Final Cut Pro is made by Apple , it will always receive the better treatment compared to other softwares.

Professional grade video editing software with 8 live cameras viewer  &amp; also support of editing Uncompressed 4k at 60Fps videos all at the expense of beefy hardware &amp; big bucks.

**Application Link:**

[http://www.apple.com/us/final-cut-pro/](http://www.apple.com/us/final-cut-pro/)
